description.excerpt: This project uses TensorFlow2.0 for image classification tasks.
A TensorFlow_2.0 implementation of AlexNet and VGGNet.

invocation.excerpt: To evaluate the model's performance on the test dataset, you can run evaluate.py.

requirement.excerpt:
+ **Python 3.x** (My Python version is 3.6.8)
+ **TensorFlow version: 2.0.0-beta1**
+ The file directory of the dataset should look like this:
``` ${dataset_root} |——train | |——class_name_0 | |——class_name_1 | |——class_name_2 | |——class_name_3 |——valid | |——class_name_0 | |——class_name_1 | |——class_name_2 | |——class_name_3 |——test |——class_name_0 |——class_name_1 |——class_name_2 |——class_name_3 ```
